    srs-kg:structure "Verb + 不 + Verb; Subj. + Verb + 不 + Verb + Obj.; Adj. + 不 + Adj.; [First Char of Verb/Adj] + 不 + [Whole Verb/Adj]; Subj. + 有没有 + Obj." .

srs-inst:gp-a1-011-the-also-adverb-ye-%E4%B9%9F a srs-kg:GrammarPoint ;
    rdfs:label "The 'also' adverb 'ye' (也)"@en ;
    srs-kg:cefrLevel "A1" ;
    srs-kg:explanation "The adverb 也 (yě) translates to 'too' or 'also' and is always placed after the subject and before the verb or adjective. In negative sentences, it is used for 'either' and comes before the negative particle (like 不 or 没). When used with adjectives that require an adverb like 很 (hěn), 也 is placed before that adverb. To express 'me too', a complete phrase like 我也是 (wǒ yě shì) is used, as 也 cannot end a sentence."@en ;
    srs-kg:hasExample srs-inst:sent-gp-a1-011-the-also-adverb-ye-%E4%B9%9F-001,
        srs-inst:sent-gp-a1-011-the-also-adverb-ye-%E4%B9%9F-002,
